---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { NAME, EMAIL, PHONE, ADDRESS, CITY, COUNTY, POSTCODE, COMPANY_NO } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout title="Terms and Conditions">
  <main class="container my-5">
    <h1>Terms and Conditions</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      These terms and conditions govern your use of this website and any booking or enquiry you make with {NAME}.
      By using this website or requesting our services, you agree to these terms.
    </p>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>1. Company Information</h2>
      <p>
        {NAME} (Company No: {COMPANY_NO}) operates this website and provides mobile tyre services.
      </p>
      <p>
        Registered service address: {ADDRESS}, {CITY}, {COUNTY} {POSTCODE}.
      </p>
      <p>
        Contact: <a href={`mailto:${EMAIL}`}>{EMAIL}</a> or <a href={`tel:${PHONE}`}>{PHONE}</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>2. Services</h2>
      <p>
        We provide mobile and emergency tyre services, including fitting, replacement, puncture repair and related roadside support.
        Service availability, response times and outcomes depend on location, traffic, weather, stock and vehicle condition.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>3. Quotes and Pricing</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Quotes are provided based on the information you give us at the time of enquiry.</li>
        <li>Final charges may vary if circumstances differ on arrival, including tyre size/specification or additional work required.</li>
        <li>Unless stated otherwise, prices are in GBP and include applicable UK taxes.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>4. Bookings and Cancellations</h2>
      <p>
        By booking a service, you confirm that you are authorised to request work on the vehicle and that the information supplied is accurate.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Please notify us promptly if you need to cancel or reschedule.</li>
        <li>
          Where a technician has already been dispatched, we may charge a reasonable call-out fee to cover time and travel costs.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>5. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide a safe and legal location for work to be carried out.</li>
        <li>Ensure we have clear access to the vehicle and wheel fixings.</li>
        <li>Disclose known issues that may affect the service, including damage or missing parts.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        We may refuse or pause service where safety concerns or legal restrictions apply.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>6. Payment</h2>
      <p>
        Payment is due when the service is completed unless otherwise agreed in writing. We may withhold release of the vehicle or related documentation
        until payment is received.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>7. Warranty and Liability</h2>
      <p>
        We perform services with reasonable care and skill in line with UK consumer law. Nothing in these terms excludes or limits liability where it
        would be unlawful to do so.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>We are not responsible for delays caused by events outside our reasonable control.</li>
        <li>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, we are not liable for indirect or consequential losses, including loss of income or business interruption.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>8. Website Use</h2>
      <p>
        Content on this website is provided for general information only. We may update, suspend or withdraw website content at any time without notice.
        You must not misuse this site, attempt unauthorised access or use content in a way that infringes intellectual property rights.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>9. Governing Law</h2>
      <p>
        These terms are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Any dispute will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of England and Wales.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-4">
      <h2>10. Changes to These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update these terms from time to time. The latest version will always be published on this page.
      </p>
      <p class="mb-0"><strong>Last updated:</strong> 30 April 2026</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>